\right)∂Sh​∂L​=−i∑​Pi,h​​∂Si,h​∂L​−j∈{1,…,Nk​}∑​Pij​∂Sij​∂L​​ Where: Simplified Gradient: Since the sink is computed but not used in the output, its gradient ∂L/∂Si,h= 0. Therefore, the backward equation simplifies to: ∂L∂Sh=−∑iPi,h(∑j∈{1,…,Nk}Pij∂L∂Sij)\frac{\partial L}{\partial S_h}
=
